<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1343,1513]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Remarks.—A small (body length about 
<quantity box="[592,672,1343,1369]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
, fore wing length about 
<quantity box="[939,1018,1343,1369]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
) black and green species with significant pile. The approximately triangular head and prothorax, infuscation on the distal fore wing radius anterior 1 and radius anterior 2, and the radial crossvein extending onto the radius anterior 2 and radius posterior veins, and short opercula not covering tympanal cavity can be used to distinguish the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1343,1513]" box="[199,1232,1486,1513]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Distribution.—The species is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[735,870,1487,1513]" name="Madagascar" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A." box="[885,1219,1486,1513]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" refId="ref68709" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A. (1985) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica 34. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrect, 414 pp." type="book" year="1985">Duffels &amp; van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
